        "mechanics_understanding": "The player controls a piece that can move in four directions. Each move costs stamina. Walls block movement, and attempting a blocked move wastes a turn without changing position. Special modifier tiles (shape, color, rotation) alter the piece's attributes when stepped on: shape cycles through 6 shapes, color cycles through orange, blue, green, red, and rotation increases by 90\u00b0 clockwise (wrapping around). Goal cells become activated only when the piece's current shape, color, and rotation exactly match the goal's requirements. Stepping onto an activated goal completes it. Completing all goals in a level advances to the next. Stamina reaching zero causes the player to lose a life and resets stamina; losing all lives ends the game."
